article.headline: Old Dominion 87, James Madison 69
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Arnaud Dahi and Drew Williamson combined for 28 points to lead Old Dominion to a 87-69 win over James Madison Saturday night. The Monarchs (16-7, 9-4 Colonial Athletic Association) had six players scoring in double-digits, including Dahi and Williamson with 14 points each. Old Dominion went on a 13-3 run against the Dukes (3-17, 0-12) within the first five minutes of play. James Madison took the lead only once in the game on a layup by Joe Posey that put the Dukes up 20-19 with 9:19 left in the first half. The Monarchs quickly recovered, ending the half up 49-31. The Monarchs took their largest lead of the game on a 3-pointer by Abdi Lidonde, putting Old Dominion up 87-56 with 2:52 to play. The Dukes were kept to 38 percent shooting, while Old Dominion went 56 percent from the field, including 10-of-19 from the 3-point range. Valdas Vasylius had 13 points and eight rebounds for the Monarchs, Brian Henderson added 12, and Alex Loughton and Lidonde each had 10. Juwann James led James Madison with 16 points, Posey added 14, and Kyle Swanston had 11.
